# API surface manifest

Versions: v1.0.0, v2.0.0.

Everything is declared in the version where it first appeared or changed;
between those versions it is inherited unchanged through the chain — so
absence from a version directory's text does NOT mean absence from that
version's surface. This manifest is the greppable record: an entry exists in
every version from its introduction until (if ever) listed as removed.
Changes are labeled "(docs)" when only documentation changed and "(via
referenced types)" when the entry itself is identical but a type it references
was re-declared; unlabeled changes are structural.

## Methods and events

| Name | Kind | History |
|------|------|---------|
| iscsi.fetch | call | introduced v1.0.0 |
| test.changed | event | introduced v1.0.0; changed v2.0.0 (via referenced types) |
| test.create | call | introduced v1.0.0; changed v2.0.0 (via referenced types) |
| test.get | call | introduced v1.0.0 |
| test.query | call | introduced v1.0.0; changed v2.0.0 (via referenced types) |
| test.remove | call | introduced v2.0.0 |
| test.remove | event | introduced v2.0.0 |
| test.run | job | introduced v1.0.0 |
| test.update | call | introduced v1.0.0 |

## Types

| Name | Kind | History |
|------|------|---------|
| ISCSIThing | type | introduced v1.0.0 |
| KindEnum | type | introduced v1.0.0 |
| TagChoice | type | introduced v1.0.0 |
| TestChangedAddedEvent | type | introduced v1.0.0; changed v2.0.0 (via referenced types) |
| TestCreate | type | introduced v1.0.0 |
| TestEntry | type | introduced v1.0.0; changed v2.0.0 |
| TestRemoveAddedEvent | type | introduced v2.0.0 |
| Widget | type | introduced v1.0.0 |
| WidgetInput | type | introduced v1.0.0 |
